               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">called</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491126-name-875" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-875" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-875" type="surname" value="BENHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-875" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN BENHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband is a labourer, at Sydenham—I have known the prisoner eight or nine months, but have known very little of her; she lodged with me three weeks—I always found her sober and honest—after she left Mrs. Whitaker's, I went there to oblige Mrs. Whitaker till she got suited—the tea and sugar I bought for the prisoner on the Saturday as she went to her new situation on the Monday—she was to have 16<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. a year, and find her own tea and sugar. <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18491126-148-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-148-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-148-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 34.—<hi rend="italic">Strongly Recommended to mercy by the Jury.—
